        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Several improvements have been made to the side mounted mirrors used on HPV Models (Figure 1).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0416031.webp" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Side Mounted HPV Mirror</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Upper Tube Connector (Holder)</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Flip Out Arm</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Pivot Spring (Lower Holder)</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Carrier Plate</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>The following refers to the numbers in Figure 1:</para>
                <para>1. Redesigned upper tube connector (holder) and longer Torx screws.</para>
                <para>2. Flip out arm rubber tip material revised to a reinforced rubber material and teeth added for
                    improved grip.
                </para>
                <para>3. New pivot spring with sleeve height designed to prevent over compression of the spring and
                    allows for better retention while maintaining break away.
                </para>
                <para>4. Redesigned carrier plate to inhibit mirror movement.</para>
